    <note type="biography">
        <p>Owner of the Mediterranean island of Monte Cristo. Purchased Monte Cristo in 1852, having been ordered to the Mediterranean for his health. In 1860, with his wife, Victorine, convicted by a Sardinian court of sedition, but granted remission of penalties. Fled to Britain and sought compensation from the Sardinian government following the sacking of Monte Cristo by Giuseppe Garibaldi’s troops.</p></note>
